Australia's **Age Pension** is a fortnightly government payment from Centrelink available to eligible residents aged 67 and over. The maximum rate is approximately **$1,144/fortnight** for singles and **$1,725/fortnight** for couples (FY2025–26), subject to assets and income tests.

Both tests are applied — Centrelink pays the lower resulting amount. For homeowners, the pension reduces when financial assets exceed $314,000 (single) or $470,000 (couple), and cuts out entirely above approximately $686,250 (single) or $1,031,000 (couple). Use this calculator to estimate your entitlement.
